--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
DESCRIPTION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This role manages curl.

cURL is a tool for getting files from HTTP, FTP, FILE, LDAP, LDAPS, DICT, TELNET
and TFTP servers, using any of the supported protocols. cURL is designed to work
without user interaction or any kind of interactivity. cURL offers many useful
capabilities, like proxy support, user authentication, FTP upload, HTTP post,
and file transfer resume.

For more detailed information on the usage and available configuration options
please consult the following sections.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
USAGE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

INSTALL
  - hosts: all
    roles:
     - role: curl
       curl_state: 'install'

REMOVE
  - hosts: all
    roles:
     - role: curl
       curl_state: 'remove'

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
VARIABLES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ROLE
  curl_state
    Description: Control the state of the role.
    Required   : False
    Value      : Predetermined
    Type       : String
    Default    : 'install'
    Options    :
      Install: 'true' | 'yes' | 'install'
      Remove : 'false' | 'no' | 'remove'

